        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-04-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="24" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d24">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Koerner</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 79.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-04-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 7, 1864</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi>Your despatch of March 20, No. 83, has been
                    received.</p>
                <p>I thank you for the perseverance you have exercised in tracing the affair of the
                    Princess to its source, and I think it proper that you should informally make
                    known to Sir John Crampton, her Britannic Majesty’s ambassador at Madrid, the
                    favorable impression which has been made upon this government by the directness
                    and frankness with which he has made known to you the information which he
                    possessed upon that subject. I shall take occasion to address myself in the same
                    sense to her Britannic Majesty’s government.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gustavus Koerner</hi>, Esq., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>., &amp;<hi rend="italic">c</hi>.<hi rend="italic">, Madrid.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
